Looks like there is a typo of a lowercase m in the classname
for  Line 33 of org.apache.batik.util.Messages.java:

    protected final static String RESOURCES =
        "org.apache.batik.util.resources.messages";

Should have a capital M in messages:

    protected final static String RESOURCES =
        "org.apache.batik.util.resources.Messages";

Seems to potentially manifest itself with a resource not found exception
though in some cases it works because of certain case-insensitive coding?
